heading: furnished beautiful garden duplex in brownstone 3BR/BA
body: We are the owners of a beautiful brownstone in Bushwick. We live in the ground floor apartment, a duplex with 3 bathrooms, 3 bedrooms, a backyard, washer/dryer, and a huge kitchen. We plan to travel for the next few years (indefinitely) and so are looking to sublet our apartment. We would treat it as a standard rental agreement, except that all utilities are included for a $300 monthly fee (gas, water, electric, heat, tv, wireless internet, local phone, and alarm system!) The space will be furnished with the basics. Across the street is a park so there is lots of light coming in both sides of the apartment. The neighbors are all very friendly and it is generally a quiet block nearest the J train and the B52 but also a reasonable walk to the L. We would be interested in signing a lease of 1 year. We will require proof of income, $3200 security deposit, and additional pet deposit (pets approved on a case by case basis.) Please no brokers or other solicitations in response to this ad/post. Thanks! Available March 1st.

heading: Gran lujo 1BR Gimnasio Lavandera con consejera cubierta
body:
A Wonderful 1 dormitorio y vistas de privilegio en Greenpoint Norte Brooklyn. Este alquiler tiene todo lo que usted pide en serio. Las cocinas cuentan con acero inoxidable de alta gama y electrodomésticos con calificación Energy Star, encimeras de cuarzo. Lavavajillas y microondas en cada apartamento. El baño cuenta con accesorios elegantes, encimeras de cuarzo, duchas con baldosas de metro. Arandelas de tamaño completo y secador en muchas habitaciones apartments.Laundry en cada piso. (Sí, has leído bien) Este edificio verde es LEED Certified tiene cancelación de ruido ventanas. La zona es ciclista amistoso con un montón de caminos en bicicleta a lo largo. Varios modos de transporte de estar cerca del metro, tres líneas de autobús y ferry. Cuando se calienta incluso se puede caminar por el puente Pulaski por el pie y la cabeza a Queens. El barrio cuenta con uno de la mejor vida nocturna en Brooklyn con bares y restaurantes. El edificio es un diseño de la posguerra que se mezcla muy bien con algunos de los históricos edificios industriales vecinos. Además, estás cerca de Williamsburg, Long Island City, Bushwick, Union Square y Midtown menos de 15 minutos
Grandes instalaciones son sala de bicicletas . Garaje . Courtyard . Sala de fitness . Salón ,
Azotea ajardinada terraza con una con unas vistas preciosas de Manhattan y de Brooklyn .
Instalaciones del área de trabajo , incluyendo sala de conferencias, estaciones de ordenador , Wi-Fi de alta velocidad, y la impresión de punto de acceso
De alta velocidad Wi-Fi gratuito en todas las zonas comunes interiores y exteriores.
Me numbero es 347-497-2429 Llame para ver esta apt. Yo vivo en la zona o en mejores palabras que soy residente de toda la vida en la zona, así que totalmente sé lo que estoy hablando!

heading: Immense  Immaculate Bed Stuy 2 or 3 BR off A/C or J  NO FEE
body:
This sprawling, tastefully renovated 2 Bedroom Bed Stuy Apartment located 5 blocks from the Ralph C, 5 blocks from the Halsey J and 7 blocks from the Utica Ave A/C is rife with large bright windows on the top floor of a 2 floor building. It can easily be used as a 3 Bedroom though the common space near the kitchen, while more than adequate for a living room arrangement, is less sizable than the other possible common space, and one roommate would end up with the biggest bedroom I`ve ever seen in NYC. It`s surrounded by a vast selection of restaurants, nightlife and shopping of all sorts. Personal favorites include Peaches Modern Comfort Food & Therapy Wine Bar.
The particulars...
• Lovely new wood floors and new paint
• Brand new Appliances including DISHWASHER
• 2 nearly identical, sizable Bedrooms w/ big bright windows. No arguments over the good one.
• Unusually MASSIVE Living Room with tons of natural light & closets. Break out the sectionals.
• Pet friendly
No Fee
First & Last Month`s rent plus One month security to move in
Strong credit and income ideal, but Guarantors also accepted

anytime to take the nickel tour.

heading: Gorgeous prewar 3-BR w/ heat  hot H2O incl Nostran A/C right there
body:
Hey!
This is an awesome apartment located on the 3rd floor of a walk-up, prewar building. Loads of cool details. The neighborhood is awesome! Tons of bars and restaurants to walk to on Franklin Ave and Lewis Ave and very close to the Nostrand A/C trains!
One of the bedrooms is railroaded, but there are multiple entrances to the apartment. If you don`t know what "railroaded" means, it means you have to walk through that room from the front bedroom to access the rest of the apartment. However, the front bedroom has a door to the hallway, so you can go around through the hallway to the other front door of the apartment. Not the most ideal for 3 roommates, but I`ve seen a lot of people make it work nicely.

-Heat+hot water included

heading: distinctive high-rise apartment building
body:
180 Montague is a distinctive high-rise apartment building set in the historic Brooklyn Heights neighborhood, putting you in the heart of eclectic and independent shopping, eateries and entertainment. This 33-story soaring tower building features a traditional red brick facade and many of the homes on the upper floors offer stunning views of Lower Manhattan as well as the Harbor. Homes may also offer vistas of the Statue of Liberty, Park Slope and the Brooklyn Bridge. Within the homes you`re greeted with spaces that are bright and open with the windows and views really taking center stage. The kitchens have been updated and include stainless steel appliances and sleek custom cabinetry with brushed nickel hardware. The common areas at 180 Montague include a stylish rooftop deck with spaces for relaxing and entertaining and there are also several indoor lounge areas for residents within the building.
 180 Montague St Brooklyn, NY 11201

With its sweeping skyline views of New York City and its rich, original history, Greenpoint is culture, commerce and community. Thoughtful and diverse apartment layouts. Kitchens featuring high-end stainless steel and Energy Star-rated appliances, quartz countertops and custom cabinetry. Bathrooms featuring stylish fixtures, quartz countertops, hardwood vanities and oversized showers with subway tile. Designer lighting, finishes and fixtures in each apartment. Dishwasher and microwave in each apartment, full-size washers and dryers in many apartments. K&auml;hrs light oak hardwood flooring throughout. Custom, spacious closets in each apartment. Grand lobby with 18&rsquo; ceilings, full-time concierge and reception lounge. Resident lounge and cyber caf&eacute; with media center, espresso bar, and entertaining kitchen. Huge courtyard with an outdoor kitchen featuring lush landscaping and ample seating areas for relaxing or entertaining. Furnished and landscaped rooftop terrace with sweeping Manhattan &amp; Brooklyn views. Fully equipped fitness center with the latest cardio, strength and CrossFit equipment. Workspace amenities including conference room, computer stations, complimentary high-speed WiFi, and hotspot printing and scanning services. Free high-speed Wi-Fi throughout all indoor and outdoor common areas. Docking stations in each amenity area for a personalized music experience. On-site garage parking with direct building access, ZipCar and ZipVan. Building Link system for packages,dry cleaning and valet notification. All residences and indoor/outdoor common areas are smoke-free. Convenient access to Brooklyn&rsquo;s best dining, shopping and entertainment. heading: True 4br in Park Slope
body:
Beautiful TRUE 4br/1ba in Park Slope at 5th and Union. Available March 15. NO BROKER FEE, WE AREN`T BROKERS WE JUST NEED TO RENT THIS APARTMENT. I don`t believe the landlord has any sort of application fee, but I will confirm that.
Location: heart of park slope at 5th and Union. One block from the R Union stop and a short walk to the trains at Barclays Center. Surrounded by amenities. Location speaks for itself.
Building: three story walk-up. Recently gut renovated. There are three other units in the building and shops at ground level.
Unit: four bedrooms all with their own windows (a true four bedroom). All the rooms can fit queen sized beds. The beds shown in the photos are all full-sized; a queen won`t fit sideways in most of them. ALL the rooms have good sized closets. High ceilings. Most of the rooms are recently painted. Ceiling fan in the living room. Gas heat/stove/oven. Good water pressure. Toilet was recently rebuilt (all new parts inside). There is no "master bedroom" so everyone has a fair space.
The Deal: we have lived here for nearly three years and will be moving on. In order to let us out of our month-to-month lease (without giving 60 days notice), our LL wants us to find people to take over the unit. So, you should be prepared to prove income (typically a salary equal to 40x the monthly rent), bank statements, credit, etc.

heading: Come and Get Me Baby
body:
Okay, We all know how hard it is to find love these days especially on Craigslist. Am I right?
I`m a Sunny suite on the top floor (Two flights up) of a brick townhouse.
I have:
One Junior Bedroom (approx 7`x9`)
A Large Living Room (approx 12`x 14`)
A Large Eat in Kitchen
A Spacious Bathroom
I`m comfortable enough for two! A cosy old soul you can cuddle up with.
What I`m not: I`m NOT a high roller, which means I have:
No Doorman
No Con siege
No Elevator
No Laundry on premises
No Rooftop/Backyard access
No Swimming Pool
No Gym
No On Site Parking ...
Yeah, I`m old but I`ll treat you right. Trust me, I`m faithful and I have all you need.
I`m an old soul who`s been around the block and is truly a diamond in the rough. Make me your own today!
I`m perfectly located!! Bergen Street between 5th Avenue and Flatbush Avenue.
Literally steps away from everything!!
BAM, bars, cafes, restaurants, Prospect Park, all trains imaginable.
Barclays Center 1 block away. Endless possibilities...
My Rent includes Heat and Water. You will be responsible for Electricity and Cooking gas.
Also Needed: One month rent and one month security along with a verifiable source of income.
If you`re easy going and low maintenance I might be the right match for you!
Good Luck with your search :)

heading: Vintage apt  shared yard  Wifi
body:
It`s the first floor of an owner-occupied three-family. I`m the owner and live on the second floor.
The apartment has high ceilings, six windows, two entrances, four big rooms, bathroom with shower, and a large closet. It`s wider than most railroad apartments. I listed it last month, but the photos were nicer than the apartment, so I took it off the market and improved it so much that now the apartment is nicer than the photos. (These are the old images. Kitchen floor has been prettied-up. Tenant may choose final finish - poly or paint.) However, please note that it`s not a "renovated" apartment.
The third-floor tenants are gung-ho about growing a garden in the neglected backyard. There`s plenty of room for more gardeners or landscape artists :)
The apartment is spacious, but like most railroad apartments hereabouts, it`s not a "true" two bedroom. However, there are several ways to create private space for each of two roommates.
I MAY allow some airbnb -- but only the legal way and subject to my vetting and rules. We would cooperate and share the income. My apartment has a similar layout and I`ve been wanting to do airbnb myself -- so, I`ve already thought out a lot of the angles. When I offered this possibility for the third floor, some people went kinda nuts and scared me off the idea. So, I want to be clear that this is an opportunity, NOT a right.
The neighborhood is sweet, quiet, and very safe. There`s a laundromat on the corner and many coffee shops, restaurants, and mom & pop grocers nearby. You can walk to Williamsburg in 15 minutes, join the excitement, and return to tranquility. The Nassau Ave. G-subway stop is about a half mile away and the Graham Ave. L stop is .9 mile`s away. The B48 bus stops at my corner and takes you straight to the Lorimer L-train. A taxi to or from Penn Station is about $22 + tip, less if you`re going downtown. But for local travel, in good weather, biking is best.
$2100/month. One month security + last month`s rent ($4200) upon signing of lease (this is a kind of credit check). First month`s rent upon move-in. I`m happy to give keys earlier so tenant(s) can help me w finishing touches, paint new colors &/or "customize" before actual move-in -- but only if first month is paid.
Send me an e-mail that tells me a little about yourself(selves). If the B&B idea interests you, a resumé would be helpful.
Cats are welcome. Dogs maybe.
